review_blob: [CASK: The Waterhouse, Manchester 24/04/07] Reasonable middle range ale that lacked excitment that my perception had build up from the name. Not to shabby but could have been so much more.

[CASK: The Waterhouse, Manchester 26/04/07] Kinda weak but not horrendious. Definatly could have been more flavoursome. Not horrible just nothing very nice. At the end of the day it went down the hatch reasonable well.
[CASK: The Waterhouse, Manchester 24/04/07] A pretty strong dark ale that was pleasant and worth it. Flavour could have been a bit more tastful, overall not bad!

[CASK: The Waterhouse, Manchester 24/04/07] Wow this was good. A full strong beautiful Belgium Ale that was the loopiest of Loopy Juices Awsome. YOU MUST TRY THIS IF YOU CAN FIND... Is a little harsh but will wet your whistle!

[CASK: The Waterhouse, Manchester 24/04/07] A please to drink after a run of bad tasting ales (must have been picking the wrong ones)!! Nothing too amazing but overall nice and pleasant! Definatly one that you can knock back with ease! Worth trying if you find it.

[CASK: The Waterhouse, Manchester 24/04/07] Think I want to cry. Titanic were becomeing one of the brewers I was pleased to see on a pump clip as I breezed in the pub door. This ale however was a total shocked!! Weak and bad tasting. The first ale i tried in the Wetherspoons Ale Festival (23rd April - 7th May 2007). Not a good one to start on.
[CASK: The Waterhouse, Manchester 18/04/07] For a strongish ale was expecting more. Not unpleasant just nothing great. Another fruity brew with no real excitment.
[CASK: The Waterhouse, Manchester 18/04/07] A fruty ale tha\t has nothing special to rave about. Medium drinking enjoyment from a reasonableish ale. Only fair!

[CASK: The Waterhouse, Manchester 18/04/07]
A dissapointing brew from Titanic. A mediocre and nothing flashy. Shame as Titanic have produced some great treats for my tastebuds in the past.

[CASK: Font Bar, Manchester 17/04/07]
This is a 10th year anniversary brew that I have to say doesnt promise much for celebration. Very citrusy flavoured and quite overpowering. Nice if you like you fruity zesty ale but not my cup of tea!
[CASK: The Lass-O-Gowry, Manchester 17/04/07] Not a bad brew easy drinking and fairly tasty. An ale that can be drunk all night.
[CASK: Font Bar, Manchester 13/04/07] Not bad, but just a middle range IPA. Not very special. Strong citrus flavour and pretty perfumy to.
[CASK: The Waterhouse, Manchester 13/04/07] Pretty grim. Pale and nasty. Not a good experiance!!
[BOTTLED: 03/08/06] Not bad, strong and quite good flavour. Overall not bad but not too exciting either.
[CASK: The Bulls Head, Piccadilly, Manchester 12/04/07] Enjoyed this slightly more from the cask than I did the bottle. quite strong and flavoursome. A good ale and worth a try. Quite pleasant.
[CASK: The Bulls Head, Piccadilly, Manchester 06/04/07] Not bad ale, a pleasant taste. Worth a try if you come across it. Easy drinking.
[CASK: The Bulls Head, Piccadilly, Manchester 06/04/07] Absolutly delicious. A fantastically tasty ale. Exreamly pleasant and highly recommended. A must ust try!!

[CASK: The Bank, Manchester 04/04/07] 
Mediocre and not very tasty. About as reasonable as they come.
[CASK: The Brittons Protection, Manchester 01/04/07] A poor tasting cask ale and weak. was expecting so much more. No real taste.
[CASK: The Brittons Protection, Manchester 31/03/07] A nice light ale that is refreshing and has a good pleasant taste. Easy drinking and enjoyable.
[CASK: The Waterhouse, Manchester 31/03/07] A pretty poor ale. Not very tast and quite hard drinking. Overall was not the worst but had far far better.
[CASK: The Bulls Head, Piccadilly, Manchester 26/03/07] A great tasting ale that was full of flavour and a great drinking experiance. Do try as its worth it.
[CASK: The Bulls Head, Piccadilly, Manchester 26/03/07] A good tasty ale from Titanic. This brewery is getting better in my opinion with every ale I try. Good stuff!
[CASK: The Salisbury Ale House, Manchester 17/03/07] A dark brw that overall was OK. It went down, put it that way. Nothing special.
[CASK: The Station Hotel, Altrincham 17/03/07] A pretty good ale that has a nice taste. Worth a try.
[BOTTLED: 07/03/07] Think I enjoyed this a tiny bit more of the cask, but still an excellent ale and just because it was bottle made not much difference at all. Very tasty and a pleasure to drink.

[CASK: The Faulkners, Altrincham, 17/03/07] I consumed alot of ale on St Patricks Day this year but was delighted to come across an old favorite on Cask. This is one of my all time favorite ales and is a delicous dark and strong ale. A must try.

[CASK: The Gray Horse Inn, Manchester 12/03/07] Number 2 of the Inn Tune with Hydes series and not bad. A pleasant ale but so far has been my least favorite series ale I have tasted by Hydes. Worth trying while its around though and it did get better the more I drank it.

[CASK: The Lass-O-Gowry, Manchester 11/03/07] This is part of a series of Soul Legands ales. Number 2 of 12 (February 2007) in honor of Tony Clarke - This unfortunatly was nothing special. Not very flavoursome or tasty.
[CASK: The Lass-O-Gowry, Manchester 11/03/07] Reasonable taste and overall not too bad just not great.
[CASK: The Salisbury Ale House, Manchester 06/03/07] A middle of the pack ale. Nothing special here but not horrible.
[BOTTLED : 28/02/07] Not as good as it was from the cask but still a nice pleasant ale with good flavour and an overall satifying taste.

[CASK: The Albert, Southport 06/03/07] This was my 100th cask ale that I tried and wow a great one to mark the milestone. A good flavour and a very good example of British ale - What more can you expect from Britains oldes brewer. Definatly worth trying.
[BOTTLED: 04/04/07] Nothing special, not much taste to it and little flavour. Overall mediocre.
[CASK: The Bulls Head, Piccadilly, Manchester 05/03/07] Not very impressive. A resanoble ale but middle range. Nothing special, not much flavour or taste.
[CASK: The Bulls Head, Piccadilly, Manchester 05/03/07] A gorgeous pint and extreamly tasty. A good example of ale. Definatly recommended.
[CASK: The Brunswick, Piccadilly, Manchester 26/02/07] Grim... Oh why did I do it to myself. Not a good mild at all. Tasteless and horrible. The worst drink I have ever had so far!
[CASK: The Bulls Head, Piccadilly, Manchester 19/02/07] A good strongish ale that has a nice taste. Worth trying.

[CASK: The Lass-O-Gowry, Manchester 18/02/07] A poor bitter and definatly doesnt live up to its name. Manchester is a city of good ales and this is a most dissapointment! Dont bother to try you will just be let down.
[CASK: The Waterhouse, Manchester 13/02/07] A very pleasant ale that is good in flavour and overall a nice ale.
[CASK: Sinclairs Oyster Bar, Manchester 12/02/07] A great brewery and amazingly cheap prices. A very tasty bitter and very pleasant drinking.
[CASK: The Old Wellington Inn, Manchester 12/02/07] A great ale with a good flavour. Nice and very easy drinking. One of my alll time favorite ales. Do try otherwise your missing out in my opinion.
[BOTTLED: 03/01/07] A nice strong bottled ale that was very enjoyable. This is one of my favorite ales but I did enjoy it even more from the cast. Overall a greate ale. Highly recommended.
[CASK: The Lass-O-Gowry, Manchester 10/02/07] Yuk. A unpleasant ale with a bad taste. Not nice dont try unless you want to punish your tastebuds.

[CASK: Font Bar, Manchester 06/02/07]
A tasty quite strong ale that was a pleasant experiance. Definatly worth a try.
[CASK: The Lass-O-Gowry, Manchester 05/02/07] A bad tasting ale that was difficult to drink. A poor ale. Not recommended.

[CASK: Victoria Hotel, Withington, Manchester 04/02/07] I totally agree with the deScription of this ale... Seriously strong and definatly high strength. A beautiful winter ale and wow what a taste. You must try!
[CASK: The Lass-O-Gowry, Manchester 30/01/07] Another very delicious winter ale from Titanic. A great taste that leaves you wanting more and more. A must try... you wont be dissapointed.

[CASK: The Lass-O-Gowry, Manchester 28/01/07] A very good ale and one that is making me pleased with what Titanic brewery has to offer. A nice seasonal ale for the new year and delicious. Make sure you try if you can.
[CASK: the Old House From Home, West Didsbury, Manchester 23/01/07] The pint I had was 3.9% and was a nice mild ale. Good taste and above average. Not bad for a best bitter and worth trying.
